Peru Stocks: El Brocal, Candente, Cerro Verde, Maple, Milpo

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-16T21:14:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/peru-stocks-el-brocal-candente-cerro-verde-maple-milpo.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 1.5 percent to 19,772.00. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 1.8 percent to 2,513.38.  Mining companies fell after U.S. stocks and metals prices
declined, Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB,
said in a telephone interview.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
lead producer, plunged 11 percent to 42.01 soles.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, dropped
7.1 percent to $1.17.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a
Canadian zinc exploration company, fell 5.9 percent to 16 cents.
Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer
controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., slid 3.5
percent to 5.55 soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1
PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 3.3
percent to $38.  Fuel refiners slumped after crude futures in New York
dropped.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain â€™s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 2.4 percent to 80
centimos.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, slid 1.8 percent to $1.10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
